<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#BehaviorShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:Bab575f235306a4f3da0f1b69ea770404 .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#name> "unioningType" .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#propertyDefinition> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#Type> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
_:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The interpretations of a <code>Type</code> with <code>unioningTypes</code> are asserted to be the same as those of all the <code>unioningTypes</code> together, which are the <code>Types</code> derived from the <code>unioningType</code> of the <code>ownedUnionings</code> of this <code>Type</code>. For example, a <code>Classifier</code> for people might be the union of <code>Classifiers</code> for all the sexes. Similarly, a feature for people's children might be the union of features dividing them in the same ways as people in general."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#BehaviorShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:B2af2072f988284ec0e91a32eab3b7fa9 .
