_:B4a898f7365f1c67c087b341ad38cadb0 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "<code>Types</code> that feature this <code>Feature</code>, such that any instance in the domain of the <code>Feature</code> must be classified by all of these <code>Types</code>, including at least all the <code>featuringTypes</code> of its <code>typeFeaturings</code>.  If the <code>Feature</code> is chained, then the <code>featuringTypes</code> of the first <code>Feature</code> in the chain are also <code>featuringTypes</code> of the chained <code>Feature</code>."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ConnectorShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:B4a898f7365f1c67c087b341ad38cadb0 .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#name> "type" .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#propertyDefinition> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#type> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#Type> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
_:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "<code>Types</code> that restrict the values of this <code>Feature</code>, such that the values must be instances of all the <code>types</code>. The types of a <code>Feature</code> are derived from its <code>typings</code> and the <code>types</code> of its <code>subsettings</code>. If the <code>Feature</code> is chained, then the <code>types</code> of the last <code>Feature</code> in the chain are also <code>types</code> of the chained <code>Feature</code>."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ConnectorShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:B1a4cfcedf8ab2b48c98f9011e8ad7ab6 .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#name> "unioningType" .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#propertyDefinition> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#Type> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
_:Be3ecc299712b94f778b517c15b141f4a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The interpretations of a <code>Type</code> with <code>unioningTypes</code> are asserted to be the same as those of all the <code>unioningTypes</code> together, which are the <code>Types</code> derived from the <code>unioningType</code> of the <code>ownedUnionings</code> of this <code>Type</code>. For example, a <code>Classifier</code> for people might be the union of <code>Classifiers</code> for all the sexes. Similarly, a feature for people's children might be the union of features dividing them in the same ways as people in general."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
