<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#FeatureValueShape> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A <code>FeatureValue</code> is a <code>Membership</code> that identifies a particular member <code>Expression</code> that provides the value of the <code>Feature</code> that owns the <code>FeatureValue</code>. The value is specified as either a bound value or an initial value, and as either a concrete or default value. A <code>Feature</code> can have at most one <code>FeatureValue</code>."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#FeatureValueShape> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "FeatureValueShape"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
