_:B6a907fa40212117cc12d327469859fc8 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "<code>Types</code> that restrict the values of this <code>Feature</code>, such that the values must be instances of all the <code>types</code>. The types of a <code>Feature</code> are derived from its <code>typings</code> and the <code>types</code> of its <code>subsettings</code>. If the <code>Feature</code> is chained, then the <code>types</code> of the last <code>Feature</code> in the chain are also <code>types</code> of the chained <code>Feature</code>."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#LiteralExpressionShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:B6a907fa40212117cc12d327469859fc8 .
_:B9bd1e9a27be47c42419e8a2457ca0f5d <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
_:B9bd1e9a27be47c42419e8a2457ca0f5d <http://open-services.net/ns/core#name> "chainingFeature" .
_:B9bd1e9a27be47c42419e8a2457ca0f5d <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
