_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#name> "unioningType" .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#propertyDefinition> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#Type> .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
_:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The interpretations of a <code>Type</code> with <code>unioningTypes</code> are asserted to be the same as those of all the <code>unioningTypes</code> together, which are the <code>Types</code> derived from the <code>unioningType</code> of the <code>ownedUnionings</code> of this <code>Type</code>. For example, a <code>Classifier</code> for people might be the union of <code>Classifiers</code> for all the sexes. Similarly, a feature for people's children might be the union of features dividing them in the same ways as people in general."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#LiteralExpressionShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:Bcff81e29d2ffc5b624c83d7426ae7dca .
_:Bf01805c89ba1f71360867f86edecd411 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
