_:B0fdb5be27facf2b015b63c3b9b4d9ee7 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#Type> .
_:B0fdb5be27facf2b015b63c3b9b4d9ee7 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:B0fdb5be27facf2b015b63c3b9b4d9ee7 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
_:B0fdb5be27facf2b015b63c3b9b4d9ee7 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
_:B0fdb5be27facf2b015b63c3b9b4d9ee7 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "<code>Types</code> that restrict the values of this <code>Feature</code>, such that the values must be instances of all the <code>types</code>. The types of a <code>Feature</code> are derived from its <code>typings</code> and the <code>types</code> of its <code>subsettings</code>. If the <code>Feature</code> is chained, then the <code>types</code> of the last <code>Feature</code> in the chain are also <code>types</code> of the chained <code>Feature</code>."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#SelectExpressionShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:B0fdb5be27facf2b015b63c3b9b4d9ee7 .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#name> "unioningType" .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#propertyDefinition> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#unioningType> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#Type> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
_:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The interpretations of a <code>Type</code> with <code>unioningTypes</code> are asserted to be the same as those of all the <code>unioningTypes</code> together, which are the <code>Types</code> derived from the <code>unioningType</code> of the <code>ownedUnionings</code> of this <code>Type</code>. For example, a <code>Classifier</code> for people might be the union of <code>Classifiers</code> for all the sexes. Similarly, a feature for people's children might be the union of features dividing them in the same ways as people in general."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#SelectExpressionShape> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#property> _:B10d239feac66cdf357fd845bba20e3a2 .
