<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#SpecializationShape> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "<code>Specialization</code> is a <code>Relationship</code> between two <code>Types</code> that requires all instances of the <code>specific</code> type to also be instances of the <code>general</code> Type (i.e., the set of instances of the <code>specific</code> Type is a <em>subset</em> of those of the <code>general</code> Type, which might be the same set)."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#SpecializationShape> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "SpecializationShape"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
