<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#occurs> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-many> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#propertyDefinition> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#ownedFeatureChaining> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#range> <https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/vocabulary#FeatureChaining> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#readOnly> "false"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#representation> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#valueType> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureChaining> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The <code>ownedRelationships</code> of this <code>Feature</code> that are <code>FeatureChainings</code>, for which the <code>Feature</code> will be the <code>featureChained</code>."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#ownedFeatureInverting> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://open-services.net/ns/core#Property> .
