<https://www.omg.org/spec/kerml/20250201/shapes#source> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The resource URI a client can perform a get on to obtain the original non-OSLC AM formatted resource that was used to create this resource. The source resource is usually a binary or proprietary format that the service provider can consume and convert into an OSLC AM format. The service may use content negotiation with the Accept header to obtain the desired content type."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
